where Œ†<sub>Œ©</sub>(<italic>a</italic>)‚âîargmin<sub><italic>b</italic></sub>{‚Äñ<italic>a</italic>‚àí<italic>b</italic>‚Äñ|<italic>b</italic>‚ààŒ©} is the Euclidean projection of a vector <italic>a</italic> onto a region Œ©. We employed an approach by (Duchi <italic>et al.</italic>, <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B12">2008</xref>) which involves only simple operations such as sorting and thresholding for this projection step.</p>
